<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1912-03-28T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1912-03-28T00:00:00-05:00" n="851" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d851">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 882.51/314.</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">American Minister</gloss> to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss></hi>.</head>
                        <opener>
                            <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                        </opener>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>, <lb/>
                                    <hi rend="italic">Monrovia</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1912-03-28">
                                    <hi rend="italic">March 28, 1912</hi></date>.</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>Department’s March 27. Liberian Government to-day cabled £1,700 to their
                            Consul General at London in payment of interest on 1871 loan.
                            Investigation desired by bankers is proceeding on lines indicated by the
                            Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Crum.</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>